## v1.4.1 increment

What v1.4.1 adds on top of v1.4.0, also frozen:

  - TS-007 atomic page-save: a single-roundtrip endpoint so
    `/admin/pages/[id]` cannot land a new block array plus an
    old title. `POST /api/pages/[id]/save` accepts
    `{ meta, blocks }` and writes both inside one
    `withPgTx`. `status=published` flips
    `published_at = now()`; `status=draft` clears it. Each
    payload is schema-bounded (`meta.title|slug|seoTitle`
    200 chars, `seo_description` 500 chars, `block.data`
    200 KB). Non-trivial writes call `appendAudit("pages.save",
    ...)`.
  - `GET /api/pages/[id]/blocks` (new handler, admin-gated
    via `requireAdminSession`). Reads `page_blocks` ordered by
    `order_index ASC, id ASC`. Useful both as a smoke target
    and for clients that want to fetch the block array
    without round-tripping through the full page row.
  - `scripts/smoke-save.mjs` (new) - anon 401 on both routes,
    admin save returns `success: true` and an `audit` echo,
    follow-up GET shows the marker block round-tripped,
    atomicity probe (empty-meta save lands `saved.meta=false`),
    cleanup restores the prior block list when
    `SMOKE_SAVE_NO_RESTORE` is unset.
  - Files unfrozen for v1.4.1:
      - `src/app/api/pages/[id]/save/route.ts` (new)
      - `src/app/api/pages/[id]/blocks/route.ts` (additive
        GET handler)
      - `scripts/smoke-save.mjs` (new)

## Operator carve-out (added to v1.1.0)

The v1.1.0 release introduces operator surfaces that are **not** under the
buyer-visible freeze. These files can be added or edited to support the
superadmin console and Envato onboarding without breaking the buyer promise:

  - `src/app/superadmin/**` (operator console pages)
  - `src/app/api/operator/**` (operator-only routes)
  - `src/app/api/envato/webhook/route.ts` (Envato purchase intake)
  - `src/components/operator/**` (operator-only components)
  - `src/lib/operator-store.ts` (operator data layer)
  - `src/lib/operator-auth.ts` (operator cookie session)
  - `src/lib/tenant-brand.ts` (tenant brand + palette reader)

These surfaces are gated by `SUPERADMIN_EMAIL` + `SUPERADMIN_PASSWORD` env vars.
